2. NEW CASES: non-hubei areas in China continue to drop firmly and are expected to return to zero in the near future

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure 2

Non-hubei new cases in China continue to drop steadily. New Growth is almost back to zero.

A netizen asks why to want to say"firm"drop? It should be noted that an infectious disease with an R 0 value of 2-3, if not effectively controlled, must be accelerating in an explosive manner. According to the median value of 4 days of the new Virus latency, after about 10 days, it should have been time from February 3 that the second, third and even fourth generation cases could have piled up, however, we have seen that the number of new cases in non-hubei areas in China has not continued to increase but started to decrease.

That can only lead to the conclusion that the path of the virus has been effectively blocked. This is the result of effective prevention and control measures in place, so we used the word "resolute" . An epidemic of this magnitude can only be contained in one of two states: contained or not contained. If it's not contained, it will explode, and in a very short period of time, it will reach a point where the numbers can't cover it. It's under control. It's under control. The situation will improve relatively quickly. We have strong confidence in the control of the epidemic in non-hubei areas.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

Because the 13,332 clinical cases published in Hubei on February 12 do not represent a comparable increase in the previous day's stock, either forward or backward. So we switch from the 13th. But no matter press old caliber or new caliber, Hubei non-wuhan area's figure is too good to be believed, the following trend, might as well see tomorrow.

6. The number of hospitalizations in non-hubei areas of the country peaked

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
10

Today, we use "the current number of confirmed cases in china-the current number of confirmed cases in Hubei" to introduce "the current number of confirmed cases in non-hubei areas in China" , this is a direct replacement of the "number of non-hubei hospital treatment in China. ". We have seen a continuous decline in the number of people in hospitals in non-hubei areas since February 11. At the same time, we are still seeing "confirmed but not in hospital" cases in Hubei. They are believed to have been quarantined and given medical treatment even though they are not in hospital.

7. New Cure and case fatality rates

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure 11

The number of new cures continues to rise. The number of newly cured people in Hubei has jumped for a time, including the factors of caliber conversion and the factors of stock conversion.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
12

The number of new cases and new diagnoses in non-hubei areas of China passed the "Golden Cross" point successfully on February 12. It means that from this day on, if nothing else, nearly 10,000 hospitalizations in non Hubei areas of the country will begin to decline. Before this, domestic non-hubei area's other two important stocks "still receives the medical observation number" and "to check the suspected case" has successively peaked to drop. Since these three stocks (as we have stated in the case of outbreak 0211) correspond to huge medical and social resources, their overall peak decline is undoubtedly a "critical inflection point" for the overall situation of the war!

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
13

According to the new standard, the case-fatality rate in Hubei has been reduced, which should be caused by the mild condition and low case-fatality rate of the "clinical diagnosed cases" . The case fatality rate in non-hubei areas of the country is still slowly increasing, which is also normal: Because of the increase in new cases admitted to hospital every day in the early stage of the outbreak, after a period of time lag, the number of deaths will increase rapidly as the disease progresses; at the same time, as the outbreak is brought under control, the number of newly confirmed cases per day will decrease significantly and the cumulative rate of confirmed cases will slow down. This fast (numerator) and slow (denominator) leads to a slow rise in the case fatality rate. It is only when the epidemic is largely over that the figure approaches the "final case fatality rate" .

Summary: non-hubei areas of China's new cases are expected to return to zero around February 20, that is, the cumulative confirmed cases of the "top. ". Hubei and Wuhan entered the stage of general offensive in the defensive war.
